In [this](http://jsfiddle.net/dqmcnt16/1/) jsfiddle it will render an `<a>` with the text "Link" and another label that says "Toggle". When you click Toggle it changes the state and removes the `<a>` and puts a `<text>` in it's place. Click "Toggle" again and it resets the state, but the `<a>` fails to show up.

Under Chrome (only browser I've tested) I can see the `<a>` in the dev tools, but it doesn't display on the page.

Copy of the code in the jsfiddle:

```
var Svg = React.createClass({
    getInitialState: function() {
        return {
            showLink: true
        };
    },
    renderLink: function() {
        if (this.state.showLink) {
            return (
                <a href="http://facebook.github.io">
                    <text x="0" y="20">Link</text>
                </a>
            );
        }
        return (
            <text x="10" y="20">Text</text>
        );
    },
    toggle: function() {
        this.setState({
            showLink: !this.state.showLink
        });
    },
    render: function() {
        return (
            <svg viewbox="0 0 100 100">
                {this.renderLink()}
                <text
                    onClick={this.toggle}
                    x="0"
                    y="50">
                    Toggle
                </text>
            </svg>
        );
    }
});

React.render(<Svg />, document.body);
```
